The paper deals with image processing techniques for evaluating the homogeneity of a region, which is a common topic in computer vision (cs.CV). The use of logarithmic image processing operators is also relevant to image and signal processing (cs.IM) and multimedia (cs.MM). The paper also discusses the application of these techniques to region growing algorithms, which falls under the category of graphics (cs.GR). Finally, the paper mentions the use of specific dilations, which is a technique commonly used in information theory (cs.IT).
